    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-07T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-07T20:00:00-05:00" n="159"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d159">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.00/12–445: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-07T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 7, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1243. For Grady Mission. Following summarizes note presented Dept Dec 6 by Greek
                    Amb.</p>
                <p>[Here follows summary of note from the Greek Embassy printed on <ref
                        target="#pg_186">page 186</ref>.]</p>
                <p>It is Depts understanding that Allied observers did not strongly recommend date
                    not later than March. Joint statement released in Athens (urtel 1405 Dec 4)
                    mentions hopes that there will be “no delays in connection with holding of
                    elections” but was presumably released after Govts official announcement of
                    March 31.</p>
                <p>Dept feels it essential that Greek Govt publicly acknowledge responsibility for
                    selection of date, and requests your comment on arguments contained in reference
                    note.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
